    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a 2007 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) featuring the 3.6L M96/05 flat-six engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, delivering a broad torque curve and a linear power band. The 6-speed manual transaxle provides crisp engagement through the gates, paired with a rear-wheel-drive configuration for authentic chassis feedback. This example remains mechanically robust, with recent inspection of the IMS bearing and a cooling system pressure test. The suspension geometry retains its factory precision, utilizing MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup with Bilstein dampers for exceptional lateral stability. Braking is handled by four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing minimal thermal stress. The vehicle exhibits a clean aesthetic with minor cosmetic patina appropriate for its age, making it an ideal candidate for an enthusiast driver seeking a pure, analog experience.",
